:56:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Videos</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLRwVmtr-pp06qT6ckboaOhnm9FxmzHpbY\">Jamie King</a> - Comprehensive tutorials about modern OpenGL and Qt.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-08-28T17:56:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Debug</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/baldurk/renderdoc\">RenderDoc</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/baldurk/renderdoc\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">5.4k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":5361,\"repo\":\"baldurk/renderdoc\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - RenderDoc is a stand-alone graphics debugging tool.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-08-09T00:43:19.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Videos</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLlrATfBNZ98foTJPJ_Ev03o2oq3-GGOS2\">TheChernoProject</a> - Introduction to OpenGL in C++</li>","updatedAt":"2018-05-10T03:23:15.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Libraries</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/assimp/assimp\">assimp</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/assimp/assimp\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">6.5k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":6534,\"repo\":\"assimp/assimp\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Portable library to import 3D models in a uniform manner.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-05-10T03:07:28.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Debug</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/GPUOpen-Tools/CodeXL\">CodeXL</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/GPUOpen-Tools/CodeXL\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">956</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":956,\"repo\":\"GPUOpen-Tools/CodeXL\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - AMD's tool suite that includes debugger, profiler and frame/shader analysis.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-05-10T03:05:52.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Libraries</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/stevenlovegrove/Pangolin\">Pangolin</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/stevenlovegrove/Pangolin\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">1.3k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":1289,\"repo\":\"stevenlovegrove/Pangolin\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Lightweight portable rapid development library for managing OpenGL display / interaction and abstracting video input.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-12T00:26:01.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Libraries</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/brackeen/glfm\">GLFM</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/brackeen/glfm\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">368</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":368,\"repo\":\"brackeen/glfm\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Supplies an OpenGL ES context and input events for mobile devices and the web.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T00:05:26.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Books</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/dp/0132545233\">Interactive Computer Graphics</a> by <strong>Edward Angel and Dave Shreiner</strong> - It provides several examples using OpenGL and it covers several aspects at once, but if you are trying to learn OpenGL on your own you might not find this helpful.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-15T23:23:07.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Libraries</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.lonesock.net/soil.html\">SOIL</a> - Tiny C library used primarily for uploading textures into OpenGL. (see <a href=\"https://bitbucket.org/SpartanJ/soil2\">SOIL2</a>)</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-02T02:12:32.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Articles</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/LWJGL/lwjgl3-wiki/wiki/2.6.1.-Ray-tracing-with-OpenGL-Compute-Shaders-%28Part-I%29\">(2014) Ray tracing with OpenGL Compute Shaders</a> by <strong>Kai Burjack</strong> - Detailed tutorial series about ray tracing using OpenGL (LWJGL).</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-02T02:10:58.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Articles</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://richg42.blogspot.com.au/2014/05/things-that-drive-me-nuts-about-opengl.html\">(2014) Things that drive me nuts about OpenGL</a> by <strong>Rich Geldreich</strong> - Constructive (or not) criticism of GL API.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-02T02:10:58.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Articles</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://duriansoftware.com/joe/An-intro-to-modern-OpenGL.-Chapter-1:-The-Graphics-Pipeline.html\">(2010) What is OpenGL?</a> by <strong>Joe Groff</strong> - Brief introduction to the building blocks of OpenGL.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-02T02:10:58.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Books</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/dp/1558603875\">A Trip Down the Graphics Pipeline</a> by <strong>Jim Blinn</strong> - Popular book that contains wealth information about the graphics pipeline, and of the best sources to learn the core concepts of Computer Graphics.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-02T02:10:58.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Books</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/dp/1439893764\">OpenGL Insights</a> by <strong>Patrick Cozzi, Christophe Riccio</strong> - Rich and comprehensive resource to learn techniques and tips, covering several advanced topics of OpenGL.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-02T02:10:58.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Books</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/dp/0321773039\">OpenGL Programming Guide</a> by <strong>Dave Shreiner, et al.</strong> - It does a good job covering the basics and providing clear reference of the API.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-02T02:10:58.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Books</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/dp/0321637631\">OpenGL Shading Language</a> by <strong>Randi J. Rost, et al.</strong> - Very clear and well written book about Shading Language. Also, it provides several explanations of writing shaders.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-02T02:10:58.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Books</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/dp/0321712617\">OpenGL SuperBible</a> by <strong>Richard S. Wright, et al.</strong> - It covers the basic concepts of computer graphics and provides clear examples using OpenGL. Definitely, it is a must for beginners.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-02T02:10:58.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Books</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/dp/1568814240\">Real-Time Rendering</a> by <strong>Tomas Akenine-Moller, Eric Haines and Naty Hoffman</strong> - It does a good job at explaining concepts for game engine, basis for game client programming as well as the necessary knowledge for understanding DirectX and OpenGL.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-02T02:10:58.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Debug</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://glsl-debugger.github.io\">GL-SL Debugger</a> - Tool for debugging OpenGL programs.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-02T02:10:58.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Debug</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/dtrebilco/glintercept\">GLIntercept</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/dtrebilco/glintercept\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">418</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":418,\"repo\":\"dtrebilco/glintercept\"}____TRA